parameters:
Village Chief Olden: Phoni will surely create a new way of
being a shrine maiden that will change us and Phoni.

Clea: It's not us who changed, we just happened to be there
by chance.

Village Chief Olden: Phoni said that there is no parent and
child who worry about returning to a parent-child
relationship.

Village Chief Olden: I still don't know what Phoni is
thinking, what she feels, and how she sees me.

Village Chief Olden: Still, I hope that Phoni, who I care
about, will find happiness, even if just a little.

Clea: I think that's exactly the parent-child relationship.
It's the same feelings that my father and mother had for
me.

Village Chief Olden: I hope you will continue to get along
with Phoni and be aware of her from now on.

Village Chief Olden: I will continue to pray for the safety
of your journey and for the peace of your parents' souls.
Shrine Maiden Phoni: Clea-san, may I have a moment?

Shrine Maiden Phoni: Would you like to have a conversation
with just the two of us?
Clea: Are you all still eating?

Shrine Maiden Phoni: Um, well... it seems like someone
accidentally drank the wrong wine.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: More importantly, there's something I
want to show you, Clea-san!

Shrine Maiden Phoni: Actually, this kind of usage is not
good, but if it's gratitude towards Clea-san, my father
should forgive me.
Clea: Wow... the light is gathering.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: This is the Voice Magic that
activates plants. It comes from plants that have luminescent
pollen.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: What's interesting is that no one
knows why this voice was born or what role it serves.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: The reason for its creation in such a
long time has disappeared, leaving only the result.

Clea: It's a magnificent story, and the light is gathering
again... It's truly beautiful.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: The reason for its disappearance over
a long period of time... but for us who live in the present,
the reason is what matters most.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: Even if they say it's fleeting, I want
to convey this strong feeling...
Shrine Maiden Phoni: Clea-san, I like you.
Shrine Maiden Phoni: Well then, Clea--

Clea: You are a precious friend to me, now and forever,
from now on and always.
Clea: Nice to meet you again, Phoni.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: It's truly like you, Clea-san. I
really love that about you, you know?

Shrine Maiden Phoni: Let me say it too. Nice to meet you
again, Clea.
Clea: Hehe, it feels a little ticklish, doesn't it?

Shrine Maiden Phoni: Clea, please always reach out to me
whenever you're in trouble. I will always be on your side,
no matter what happens.

Clea: Thank you very much. At that time, I will definitely
rely on Phoni.

Clea: The wind has started to pick up a little. Let's go
back together.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: It's dazzlingly beautiful... and yet,
it's painful and heartbreaking.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: Even so, I will always be on your
side, you know.

Shrine Maiden Phoni: Clea, please wait! I will walk with
you as well.
